Leading skitmaker and comic character, Samuel Perry, aka Broda Shaggi, has promised to work harder in 2022 after a rewarding 2021. Broda Shaggi confessed to having had a rollercoaster year in 2021 as he shared a recap of the year to fans.   Shazam tips Ayra Starr for global recognition     Toke Makinwa: Bloggers obsessed with my ‘private part’     I’m a gold digger, money can buy my love, says actress…   The 28-year-old entertainer highlighted that 2021 was filled with sweet, love and betrayal but Shaggi promised to go a length more this year. “It’s been a sweet year I must say. From loving to being loved, had betrayals but stood strong. Planned all night and worked steadily all day. Loads of engagement, many laurels and recognitions. Super grateful for all I’ve achieved. Next year, we will go harder,” he noted. Broda Shaggi released more than 100 skits in 2021, featured in several Nollywood films and signed multi-million Naira endorsement deals.